

## **ONLINE EDUCATIONAL PLATFORM**
 

## Summary:

This product is intended to provide an Online Educational Platform where University Owners can publish courses and make them available to a global audience.

Given the trustless properties of the Ethereum blockchain, University Owner's doesnt need to worry about the payments hurdles, and will be able to promote a healthy business environment for content makers (course makers) and consumers (students).

  

This product enables the following functionalities:

-   Create Universities
    
-   Assign Owners to the Universities
    
-   Have the Owners create as many courses as needed with custom settings each
    
  		 Cost per course
    
		Seats available
    
  		 Other information about the course (description, website, etc)
    

-   Allow students from all around the world to pay for these courses in an easy and transparent fashion
    
-   Helps Owners keep their finances in control and withdraw funds as needed
    

  

  

## Application SETUP

  

1.  Open Ganache running on 8545    
	- Point to the new workspace (i.e.   c:\Jafett\)

2.  Connect Metamask to Ganache on 8545

		- Add Account for Platform Owner
	    - Add Account for UniOwner0    
		- Add Account for UniOwner1    
		- Add Account for Student0    
		- Add Account for UniOwner1    

3.  Setup Application
		1.  /Jafett/npm install    
		2.  /Jafett/client/npm install    
		3.  truffle.cmd deploy --compile-all --reset
    
4.  From /Jafett/client/ npm start
    
5.  this will start the application on [http://localhost:3000/](http://localhost:3000/)
    


## Using the Education Platform

1.  Setup the Education Platform as follows using the Platform Owner Account
    
		1.  Create University0	 
		2.  Create University1
		3.  Add Owner0 (from metamask mapped addresses)		    
		4.  Add Owner1 (from metamask mapped addresses)		    
		5.  Add Student0 (from metamask mapped addresses)		    
		6.  Add Student1 (from metamask mapped addresses)
    
2.  Switching from UniOwner0 and UniOwner1 to show differences in information displayed on screen.
    
3.  With UniOwner0  

			1.  Create Course U0C0 | cost 1 ETH | seats = 100
			2.  Create Course U0C1 | cost 10 ETH | seats = 10
    
![](data:image/png;base64,)
    

  

4.  Switch to UniOwner1

		1.  Create Course U1C0 | cost 5 ETH | seats = 10
		2.  Create Course U1C1 | cost 50 ETH | seats = 10
    
![](data:image/png;base64,)
    

  

5.  With STUDENT0
    
	1.  Verify the information on screen only shows available courses and no other action is possible
    
	2.  BUY 2 seats at U0C1 for a total of 20 ETH
    
		1.  You should see a transaction on MetaMask for 20 ETH		    
		2.  Confirm and verify funds adjusted accordingly in your student wallet		    
		3.  Verify that the Seats available for U0C1 is now 8 seats
    

	3.  BUY 5 seats at U0C0 for a total of 5 ETH    

		1.  You should see a transaction on MetaMask for 5 ETH		    
		2.  Confirm and verify funds adjusted accordingly in your student wallet		    
		3.  Verify that the Seats available for U0C0 is now 95 seats
    

  

6.  Switch to UniOwner0 and verify no funds has been payed to his wallet
  
		1.  The application should show information according to the Courses bought by students, 
			and the capability to withdraw funds or CLOSE a course.    
		2.  CLOSE U0C1
    

7.  Switch to STUDENT1 and reload the screen    
		
		The screen displays all courses available to buy except for U0C1
    

8.  Switch to UniOwner0
    
		1.  Withdraw the funds from U0C0 and verify the ETH was deposited to the UniOwner0 account    
		2.  Withdraw the funds from U0C1 and verify the ETH was deposited to the UniOwner0 account  
		3.  If UniOwner0 started with 100 ETH - the current balance should be ~125 ETH.
    

9.  **Go play more with other students and courses, and have fun!**
